<paragraph id="8BED0424FFF31775FF3A0E793E0EFAB2" blockId="118.[151,1436,1218,2034]" box="[199,1060,1326,1351]" pageId="118" pageNumber="119">
Etymology. The name is a noun in apposition, derived from the 
<typeStatus id="54E9BA86FFF31775FC6E0E7839E9FAB3" box="[915,963,1327,1351]" pageId="118" pageNumber="119">type</typeStatus>
locality.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BED0424FFF31775FF3A0E05398EF9EA" blockId="118.[151,1436,1218,2034]" pageId="118" pageNumber="119">
Diagnosis. Distinguished from similar congeners (other species of the 
<taxonomicName id="4C527FA7FFF31775FC120E043E75FA9F" authorityName="Simon" authorityYear="1907" box="[1007,1119,1363,1387]" class="Arachnida" family="Pholcidae" genus="Smeringopus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="118" pageNumber="119" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="thomensis">
<emphasis id="B926D836FFF31775FC120E043E75FA9F" box="[1007,1119,1363,1387]" italics="true" pageId="118" pageNumber="119">thomensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
species group) by shape of embolus (one large and one tiny apophysis arising from embolus; 
<figureCitation id="136918A1FFF31775FC610E213E6DFA7A" box="[924,1095,1398,1422]" captionStart="FIGURES 725–731" captionStartId="117.[151,258,1442,1463]" captionTargetBox="[213,1382,153,1416]" captionTargetId="figure-208@117.[175,1419,143,1416]" captionTargetPageId="117" captionText="FIGURES 725–731. Smeringopus principe (725–728) and S. mayombe (729–731). 725. Left procursus, prolateral view. 726–727, 729–730. Left emboli, prolateral and dorsal (slightly distal) views. 728, 731. Cleared female genitalia, dorsal views. Scale lines: 0.3 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6415832" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6415832/files/figure.png" pageId="118" pageNumber="119">Figs. 729, 730</figureCitation>
; similar 
<taxonomicName id="4C527FA7FFF31775FB530E213F00FA7A" authorityName="Huber" authorityYear="2012" box="[1198,1322,1398,1422]" class="Arachnida" family="Pholcidae" genus="Smeringopus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="118" pageNumber="119" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="principe">
<emphasis id="B926D836FFF31775FB530E213F00FA7A" box="[1198,1322,1398,1422]" italics="true" pageId="118" pageNumber="119">S. principe</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
); from 
<taxonomicName id="4C527FA7FFF31775FA7A0E213B2DFA47" authorityName="Simon" authorityYear="1907" class="Arachnida" family="Pholcidae" genus="Smeringopus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="118" pageNumber="119" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="thomensis">
<emphasis id="B926D836FFF31775FA7A0E213B2DFA47" italics="true" pageId="118" pageNumber="119">S. thomensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
also by pair of sclerotized areas on posterior rim of epigynum (
<figureCitation id="136918A1FFF31775FC0D0ECD3E78FA46" box="[1008,1106,1434,1458]" captionStart="FIGURES 709–717" captionStartId="115.[151,263,1495,1518]" captionTargetBox="[151,1436,191,1473]" captionTargetId="figure-188@115.[151,1436,191,1473]" captionTargetPageId="115" captionText="FIGURES 709–717. Smeringopus thomensis group. Epigyna, ventral views and cleared female genitalia, ventral and dorsal views. 709–711. S. thomensis. 712–714. S. principe. 715–717. S. mayombe." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6415826" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6415826/files/figure.png" pageId="118" pageNumber="119">Fig. 715</figureCitation>
) and wider pore plates (
<figureCitation id="136918A1FFF31775FA930ECD3AEFFA22" captionStart="FIGURES 725–731" captionStartId="117.[151,258,1442,1463]" captionTargetBox="[213,1382,153,1416]" captionTargetId="figure-208@117.[175,1419,143,1416]" captionTargetPageId="117" captionText="FIGURES 725–731. Smeringopus principe (725–728) and S. mayombe (729–731). 725. Left procursus, prolateral view. 726–727, 729–730. Left emboli, prolateral and dorsal (slightly distal) views. 728, 731. Cleared female genitalia, dorsal views. Scale lines: 0.3 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6415832" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6415832/files/figure.png" pageId="118" pageNumber="119">Fig. 731</figureCitation>
); from 
<taxonomicName id="4C527FA7FFF31775FEE60EE93BBCFA22" authorityName="Huber" authorityYear="2012" box="[283,406,1470,1494]" class="Arachnida" family="Pholcidae" genus="Smeringopus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="118" pageNumber="119" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="principe">
<emphasis id="B926D836FFF31775FEE60EE93BBCFA22" box="[283,406,1470,1494]" italics="true" pageId="118" pageNumber="119">S. principe</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
also by absence of dorsal projection from procursus tip (procursus as in 
<taxonomicName id="4C527FA7FFF31775FB1C0EE93F45FA22" authorityName="Simon" authorityYear="1907" box="[1249,1391,1470,1494]" class="Arachnida" family="Pholcidae" genus="Smeringopus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="118" pageNumber="119" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="thomensis">
<emphasis id="B926D836FFF31775FB1C0EE93F45FA22" box="[1249,1391,1470,1494]" italics="true" pageId="118" pageNumber="119">S. thomensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, cf. 
<figureCitation id="136918A1FFF31775FF6A0EB53B6BFA0E" box="[151,321,1506,1530]" captionStart="FIGURES 719–724" captionStartId="116.[151,257,1954,1975]" captionTargetBox="[300,1299,910,1935]" captionTargetId="figure-85@116.[288,1303,900,1945]" captionTargetPageId="116" captionText="FIGURES 719–724. Smeringopus thomensis. 719. Left cymbium and procursus, retrolateral view. 720. Left procursus, prolateral view. 721. Male chelicerae, frontal view. 722–723. Left embolus, prolateral and dorsal (slightly distal) views. 724. Cleared female genitalia, dorsal view. Scale lines: 0.3 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6415830" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6415830/files/figure.png" pageId="118" pageNumber="119">Figs. 719, 720</figureCitation>
). Easily distinguished from all other congeners by distinctive color pattern dorsally on abdomen (figure composed of three black elements on posterior half; 
<figureCitation id="136918A1FFF31775FCCB0D5139BDF9EA" box="[822,919,1542,1566]" captionStart="FIGURES 699–708" captionStartId="114.[151,263,1415,1438]" captionTargetBox="[156,1436,153,1388]" captionTargetId="figure-308@114.[151,1436,153,1401]" captionTargetPageId="114" captionText="FIGURES 699–708. Smeringopus thomensis group. S. thomensis (699–700, 705–706), S. principe (702–704, 707–708), and S. mayombe (701). 699, 701, 703. Males, dorsal views. 700, 702. Male prosomata, oblique frontal views. 704. Female, ventral view. 705–708. Left male palps, prolateral and retrolateral views." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6418204" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6418204/files/figure.png" pageId="118" pageNumber="119">Fig. 701</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BED0424FFF31775FF3A0D7D39DAF85E" blockId="118.[151,1436,1218,2034]" pageId="118" pageNumber="119">
Male (
<typeStatus id="54E9BA86FFF31775FEED0D7D3B53F9B6" box="[272,377,1578,1602]" pageId="118" pageNumber="119">holotype</typeStatus>
). Total body length 6.1, carapace width 1.8. Leg 1: 53.3 (13.7 + 0.8 + 12.8 + 23.7 + 2.3), tibia 2: 8.7, tibia 3: 6.1, tibia 4: 8.5; tibia 1 L/d: 60. Habitus as in 
<figureCitation id="136918A1FFF31775FCA30D1939EAF992" box="[862,960,1614,1638]" captionStart="FIGURES 699–708" captionStartId="114.[151,263,1415,1438]" captionTargetBox="[156,1436,153,1388]" captionTargetId="figure-308@114.[151,1436,153,1401]" captionTargetPageId="114" captionText="FIGURES 699–708. Smeringopus thomensis group. S. thomensis (699–700, 705–706), S. principe (702–704, 707–708), and S. mayombe (701). 699, 701, 703. Males, dorsal views. 700, 702. Male prosomata, oblique frontal views. 704. Female, ventral view. 705–708. Left male palps, prolateral and retrolateral views." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6418204" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6418204/files/figure.png" pageId="118" pageNumber="119">Fig. 701</figureCitation>
. Carapace ochre-yellow with light brown median mark and narrow lateral marks, clypeus distal half darker, sternum dark brown with small light spots, legs ochre-yellow, femora and tibiae with dark subdistal rings and light tips, abdomen grey with distinctive dorsal pattern, ventrally with dark anterior and posterior plates and three indistinct bands in median section. Distance PME-PME 125 µm, diameter PME 160 µm, distance PME-ALE 60 µm, distance AME-AME 25 µm, diameter AME 135 µm. Ocular area slightly elevated, secondary eyes with small dark ‘pseudo-lenses’; deep thoracic pit. Chelicerae with pair of small distal apophyses as in 
<taxonomicName id="4C527FA7FFF31775FD1C0C713944F8CA" authorityName="Simon" authorityYear="1907" box="[737,878,1830,1854]" class="Arachnida" family="Pholcidae" genus="Smeringopus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="118" pageNumber="119" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="thomensis">
<emphasis id="B926D836FFF31775FD1C0C713944F8CA" box="[737,878,1830,1854]" italics="true" pageId="118" pageNumber="119">S. thomensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(cf. 
<figureCitation id="136918A1FFF31775FC5F0C713E2EF8CA" box="[930,1028,1830,1854]" captionStart="FIGURES 719–724" captionStartId="116.[151,257,1954,1975]" captionTargetBox="[300,1299,910,1935]" captionTargetId="figure-85@116.[288,1303,900,1945]" captionTargetPageId="116" captionText="FIGURES 719–724. Smeringopus thomensis. 719. Left cymbium and procursus, retrolateral view. 720. Left procursus, prolateral view. 721. Male chelicerae, frontal view. 722–723. Left embolus, prolateral and dorsal (slightly distal) views. 724. Cleared female genitalia, dorsal view. Scale lines: 0.3 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6415830" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6415830/files/figure.png" pageId="118" pageNumber="119">Fig. 721</figureCitation>
). Palps in general as in 
<taxonomicName id="4C527FA7FFF31775FAF20C713FB6F8CA" authorityName="Simon" authorityYear="1907" box="[1295,1436,1830,1854]" class="Arachnida" family="Pholcidae" genus="Smeringopus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="118" pageNumber="119" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="thomensis">
<emphasis id="B926D836FFF31775FAF20C713FB6F8CA" box="[1295,1436,1830,1854]" italics="true" pageId="118" pageNumber="119">S. thomensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(cf. 
<figureCitation id="136918A1FFF31775FF380C1D3B41F896" box="[197,363,1866,1890]" captionStart="FIGURES 699–708" captionStartId="114.[151,263,1415,1438]" captionTargetBox="[156,1436,153,1388]" captionTargetId="figure-308@114.[151,1436,153,1401]" captionTargetPageId="114" captionText="FIGURES 699–708. Smeringopus thomensis group. S. thomensis (699–700, 705–706), S. principe (702–704, 707–708), and S. mayombe (701). 699, 701, 703. Males, dorsal views. 700, 702. Male prosomata, oblique frontal views. 704. Female, ventral view. 705–708. Left male palps, prolateral and retrolateral views." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6418204" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6418204/files/figure.png" pageId="118" pageNumber="119">Figs. 705, 706</figureCitation>
), procursus not distinguishable (cf. 
<figureCitation id="136918A1FFF31775FD030C1D398EF896" box="[766,932,1866,1890]" captionStart="FIGURES 719–724" captionStartId="116.[151,257,1954,1975]" captionTargetBox="[300,1299,910,1935]" captionTargetId="figure-85@116.[288,1303,900,1945]" captionTargetPageId="116" captionText="FIGURES 719–724. Smeringopus thomensis. 719. Left cymbium and procursus, retrolateral view. 720. Left procursus, prolateral view. 721. Male chelicerae, frontal view. 722–723. Left embolus, prolateral and dorsal (slightly distal) views. 724. Cleared female genitalia, dorsal view. Scale lines: 0.3 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6415830" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6415830/files/figure.png" pageId="118" pageNumber="119">Figs. 719, 720</figureCitation>
), only bulb different, with one large and one tiny dorsal processes (
<figureCitation id="136918A1FFF31775FE6A0C393868F872" box="[407,578,1902,1926]" captionStart="FIGURES 725–731" captionStartId="117.[151,258,1442,1463]" captionTargetBox="[213,1382,153,1416]" captionTargetId="figure-208@117.[175,1419,143,1416]" captionTargetPageId="117" captionText="FIGURES 725–731. Smeringopus principe (725–728) and S. mayombe (729–731). 725. Left procursus, prolateral view. 726–727, 729–730. Left emboli, prolateral and dorsal (slightly distal) views. 728, 731. Cleared female genitalia, dorsal views. Scale lines: 0.3 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6415832" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6415832/files/figure.png" pageId="118" pageNumber="119">Figs. 729, 730</figureCitation>
). Legs without spines, few vertical hairs, without curved hairs, retrolateral trichobothrium on tibia 1 at 3%; prolateral trichobothrium present on tibia 1.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BED0424FFF31775FF3A0CE13B1CF806" blockId="118.[151,1436,1218,2034]" pageId="118" pageNumber="119">
Variation. Tibia 
<quantity id="4CAAA9C1FFF31775FE7E0CE13B9BF83A" box="[387,433,1974,1998]" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="2.54" pageId="118" pageNumber="119" unit="in" value="1.0">1 in</quantity>
3 other males: 10.9, 11.3, 11.3. Posterior part of median mark on carapace sometimes barely visible.
</paragraph>
<caption id="DF2D54ACFFF21774FF6A0DE13EBCF8B7" ID-DOI="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6415834" ID-Zenodo-Dep="6415834" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6415834/files/figure.png" pageId="119" pageNumber="120" startId="119.[151,263,1718,1741]" targetBox="[151,1436,155,1695]" targetPageId="119">
<paragraph id="8BED0424FFF21774FF6A0DE13EBCF8B7" blockId="119.[151,1439,1718,1859]" pageId="119" pageNumber="120">
<emphasis id="B926D836FFF21774FF6A0DE13B44F939" bold="true" box="[151,366,1718,1741]" pageId="119" pageNumber="120">FIGURES 732–744.</emphasis>
<taxonomicName id="4C527FA7FFF21774FE8B0DEF3871F939" authorityName="Simon" authorityYear="1907" box="[374,603,1720,1741]" class="Arachnida" family="Pholcidae" genus="Smeringopus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="119" pageNumber="120" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="thomensis">
<emphasis id="B926D836FFF21774FE8B0DEF3871F939" box="[374,603,1720,1741]" italics="true" pageId="119" pageNumber="120">Smeringopus thomensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(732–740) and 
<taxonomicName id="4C527FA7FFF21774FD0A0DEF394BF939" authorityName="Huber" authorityYear="2012" box="[759,865,1720,1741]" class="Arachnida" family="Pholcidae" genus="Smeringopus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="119" pageNumber="120" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="principe">
<emphasis id="B926D836FFF21774FD0A0DEF394BF939" box="[759,865,1720,1741]" italics="true" pageId="119" pageNumber="120">S. principe</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(741–744). 732. Left male palpal femur, retrolateral view. 733. Left procursus tip, prolateral view. 734. Male cheliceral apophysis. 735. Left embolus, distal view. 736. Male gonopore. 737. Female ALS. 738. Epigynum. 739. Cleared female genitalia, dorsal view. 740. Detail of pore plate. 741. Left embolus, distal view. 742. Left procursus tip, prolateral view. 743. Cleared female genitalia, dorsal view. 744. Detail of pore plate. Scale lines: 10 µm (734, 737), 20 µm (740), 30 µm (744), 80 µm (733, 735–736), 100 µm (739, 741–742), 200 µm (732, 738, 743).
</paragraph>
</caption>
<paragraph id="8BED0424FFF21774FF3A0C383F79F83B" blockId="119.[151,1436,1903,2036]" pageId="119" pageNumber="120">
Female. In general similar to male; tibia 
<quantity id="4CAAA9C1FFF21774FD630C3838E1F873" box="[670,715,1903,1927]" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="2.54" pageId="119" pageNumber="120" unit="in" value="1.0">1 in</quantity>
<specimenCount id="9D54CFADFFF21774FD290C38397EF873" box="[724,852,1903,1927]" pageId="119" pageNumber="120" type="female">11 females</specimenCount>
: 6.7–11.3 (mean 9.7). Epigynum a simple, roughly triangular plate with pair of pockets and pair of sclerotized areas on posterior rim, transversal internal structure variably well visible, posterior plate semicircular (
<figureCitation id="136918A1FFF21774FD360CE0395AF83B" box="[715,880,1975,1999]" captionStart="FIGURES 709–717" captionStartId="115.[151,263,1495,1518]" captionTargetBox="[151,1436,191,1473]" captionTargetId="figure-188@115.[151,1436,191,1473]" captionTargetPageId="115" captionText="FIGURES 709–717. Smeringopus thomensis group. Epigyna, ventral views and cleared female genitalia, ventral and dorsal views. 709–711. S. thomensis. 712–714. S. principe. 715–717. S. mayombe." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6415826" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6415826/files/figure.png" pageId="119" pageNumber="120">Figs. 715, 716</figureCitation>
); internal genitalia as in 
<figureCitation id="136918A1FFF21774FB7E0CE03EC6F83B" box="[1155,1260,1975,1999]" captionStart="FIGURES 709–717" captionStartId="115.[151,263,1495,1518]" captionTargetBox="[151,1436,191,1473]" captionTargetId="figure-188@115.[151,1436,191,1473]" captionTargetPageId="115" captionText="FIGURES 709–717. Smeringopus thomensis group. Epigyna, ventral views and cleared female genitalia, ventral and dorsal views. 709–711. S. thomensis. 712–714. S. principe. 715–717. S. mayombe." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6415826" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6415826/files/figure.png" pageId="119" pageNumber="120">Figs. 717</figureCitation>
and 
<figureCitation id="136918A1FFF21774FADF0CE03F65F83B" box="[1314,1359,1975,1999]" captionStart="FIGURES 725–731" captionStartId="117.[151,258,1442,1463]" captionTargetBox="[213,1382,153,1416]" captionTargetId="figure-208@117.[175,1419,143,1416]" captionTargetPageId="117" captionText="FIGURES 725–731. Smeringopus principe (725–728) and S. mayombe (729–731). 725. Left procursus, prolateral view. 726–727, 729–730. Left emboli, prolateral and dorsal (slightly distal) views. 728, 731. Cleared female genitalia, dorsal views. Scale lines: 0.3 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6415832" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6415832/files/figure.png" pageId="119" pageNumber="120">731</figureCitation>
.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BED0424FFF21774FF3A0C8C3E14F807" blockId="119.[151,1436,1903,2036]" box="[199,1086,2011,2036]" pageId="119" pageNumber="120">
